Hi Filip, Thank you for confirming your ability to complete this process by September First, Im glad to share that we were able to get the approval we needed to honor DPG Medias historical Net- payment terms with Dataiku. This change will be reflected in the final executable version of our paperworkRegarding the outstanding PO and payment, given the quick timeframe to finalize this process, our finance team came up with a creative solution that will hopefully remove friction from the process for both sides. Weve simply amended the invoice language of the Order Form to the following: Dataiku will issue the credit memo for the , and an invoice for , upon execution of this Order. Dataiku will apply the Credit against any Outstanding Amounts. Following this, the Customer shall then notify Dataiku how it wishes the remaining credit amount to be applied to the above invoicesBasically this means that upon execution, Dataiku will be able to immediately invoice DPG for the outstanding . balance. However, no payment will be due because we will simply apply the credit from the new contract. So effectively, without your team having to take any action, well take care of the outstanding payment issues and your team will simply need to tell us how they would like us to apply the remaining . credit to the year and year invoices for the new subscription termThis helps us because it means we can immediately recognize this revenue in the year it was booked without having to wait for your team to issue the missing POAnd hopefully it helps you because it means your team doesnt have to scramble to generate a PO on short notice and can simply issue one single PO for the new contract amountAs soon as youre able to help us finalize the user count tomorrow, we should be in a good position to get you executable paperwork within a business day or so. Thanks! Nina Nina Birarda Account Executive nina.birardadataiku.com On Fri, Aug , at : PM Filip Beslic wrote: Hi Nina, Thanks for reaching out. The summer slowed things down a bit as we did not finish the renewal in July as expected, but Im confident that - if we can agree on maintaining DPGs historical net- payment terms - we can aim for the renewal to start september of this year. As for the volume I still need to confirm the exact amount. Given this short time-period I would advise against a separate PO as it wouldnt really make the difference. Regards Filip Filip Beslic acting Area manager data image: DPG Media Mediaplein Antwerpen T M filip.beslicdpgmedia.be dpgmedia.be On Thu, Aug at Nina Birarda wrote: Hi Filip, Apologies for bogging you down with one more thing while youre on holiday and were working to finalize our renewal. However, Im reaching out because my finance team copied has asked me to follow up with you regarding an outstanding fee due to Dataiku. We completed an add-on order in September of for the amount of . EUR. At that time, DPG only provided an PO for the amount of . EUR. Can you please ask your accounts payable team to provide the PO for the remaining amount of . EUR as soon as possible? Both the add-on order form and existing PO are attached for your reference. Our original plan was to address outstanding balance as part of the renewal process when we thought we would be able to complete the signature process in July. Also attached for easy reference. Now that more time has passed, our team is hoping to get this resolved asap. Assuming your Accounts Payable team can help with this, we can simply update the renewal paperwork to remove the mention of this balance on the first page of the Ordering Document Section. With regards to the -year renewal paperwork, I wanted to confirm that I did receive your question asking if we can honor DPGs historical net- payment terms for the upcoming renewal. I am still working to track down the approval I need for that and will keep you posted. Just so Im aware, once we clarify the payment terms, update the billing information and finalize the number of user seats, do you foresee any other review hurdles or will your team be ready to sign the renewal agreement? Thanks, Nina Nina Birarda Account Executive nina.birardadataiku.com

Hey, In bijlage opnieuw enkele kostenvergoedingen voor Vloglab. Ik kreeg ook nog van Eddy, een figurant de vraag of ik dit eens wil checken bij de boekhouding. Dus ik wil graag eens informeren of jullie hier een antwoord op hebben? Op sommige van die formulieren onkostenvergoedingquitclaims verwijst men geregeld naar art . van de en dat er een fiche . zal opgemaakt worden. Niet dat ik daar wakker van lig hoor, maar dit slaat nergens op en ik zou daar eens een deftig antwoord op willen hebben. Begrijp me niet verkeerd h, ik doe daar helemaal niet moeilijk over. Figuratie is een grijze zone. Dat fameuze art . verwijst naar belastbare beroepsinkomsten. Vermits figuratie een figurant dus geen beroep is, geen werknemer of personeelslid van een productie is en geen arbeiderscontract ondertekent, is de niet van toepassing op figuranten. Het staat trouwens duidelijk geschreven in de wet : Volgens artikel van het Wetboek van de inkomstenbelastingen WIB worden de betaalde of toegekende commissies, makelaarslonen, handels- of andere restornos, toevallige of niet-toevallige vacatiegelden of erelonen, gratificaties, vergoedingen of voordelen van alle aard, die voor de verkrijgers al dan niet in Belgi belastbare beroepsinkomsten zijn behalve bezoldigingen van meewerkende echtgenoten, maar als beroepskosten aangenomen als ze worden verantwoord door individuele fiches en een samenvattende opgave. Zou ik toch eens een antwoord krijgen? Ik begrijp anderzijds wel dat men de fiche . opmaakt om boekhoudkundig in orde te zijn. Trouwens op deze fiche wordt gevraagd het ondernemingsnummer en het beroep van de verkrijger in te vullen, maar dat is dus niet mogelijk voor een figurantSari Smeys Productie-assistent Vloglab image: PIT Medialaan Vilvoorde M sari.smeyspersgroep.net dpgmedia.be image: DPG Media
